<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,222,534]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,439,463]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is one of the most common species of porcellanid crabs in rocky habitats along the Iranian coast. Interestingly, this species has still not been recorded from the Arabian coast. 
<bibRefCitation author="Apel, M." box="[1124,1263,474,498]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" refId="ref45060" refString="Apel, M. (2001) Taxonomie und Zoogeographie der Brachyura, Paguridea und Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Decapoda) des Persisch-Arabischen Golfes. Unpublished doctoral thesis, Johann Wolfgang Goethe-Universitat, Frankfurt a. M., 268 pp." type="book" year="2001">Apel (2001)</bibRefCitation>
did not find it neither at the Saudi Arabian and nor the 
<collectingCountry box="[605,663,510,534]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">UAE</collectingCountry>
coasts in his extensive sampling.
</paragraph>
